R Jupyter Notebook for 4th and final task¶

Task detail: Retrieve matrix of gene expression for the gene IDs from previous step for sample "TCGA-A7-A13D-01A-13R-A12P-07" and "TCGA-E9-A1RH-11A-34R-A169-07" from TCGA-BRCA dataset.¶

To showcase the use of a different working tool, the latest part of the assignment was performed in R and wrapped into this Jupyter Notebook (excellent sharing and collaboration option for R and Python routines). This routine essentially uses the TCGAbiolinks R package to mine the GDC. Note that the downloaded BRCA cohort expression data were made available in the shared GitHub.

# Retrieve the gene expression data for the TCGA-BRCA dataset
query <- GDCquery(project = project, 
                  data.category = "Transcriptome Profiling", 
                  data.type = "Gene Expression Quantification", 
                  workflow.type = "STAR - Counts",
                  barcode =  samples)

# Now convert to gene symbols
rownames(data) <- mapIds(org.Hs.eg.db,
                         keys=rownames(data), 
                         column="SYMBOL",
                         keytype="ENSEMBL",
                         multiVals="first")
